Cook bacon in large saucepan until crisp, stirring frequently. Remove bacon from pan, reserving 2 Tbsp. of the drippings in pan. Discard remaining drippings; drain bacon on paper towels. Add potatoes, onion and celery to saucepan. Cook and stir 2 min. Stir in soup and milk; bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 8 min., stirring occasionally. Add remaining ingredients; cook an additional 5 min. or until process cheese food is completely melted and potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.